        "created_at": "2020-12-15T02:46:39.811Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"shubham4060\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2486\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/0ea827/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> shubham4060:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Setting the TLS paths in the network options while running the java client through Windows OS gave a TLS error but interestingly enough the same worked on a unix machine.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019m not aware of anyone else that has tried to use TLS from Windows, so sounds like there\u2019s likely a bug here.  Would you mind filing an issue for it on github?</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"shubham4060\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2486\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/0ea827/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> shubham4060:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>And also for the record layer i couldn\u2019t find any way from which the TLS paths can be set in the network options from the java client. Is there any other way to specify the tls paths in java client itself?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>There\u2019s environment variables that you can set, which are detailed in <a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/api-general.html#setting-network-options-with-environment-variables\">Setting network options with environment variables</a>.</p>",
